# Testing Conventions

## Framework & Config

- **Vitest** with V8 coverage. Thresholds: 70% lines/branches/functions/statements.
- Config files: `vitest.unit.config.ts`, `vitest.e2e.config.ts`, `vitest.live.config.ts`.

## Naming & Organization

- Tests colocated with source: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`.
- E2E tests: `*.e2e.test.ts`.
- Match source file names in test file names.

## Running Tests

```
pnpm test              # Unit tests
pnpm test:coverage     # With coverage report
pnpm test:e2e          # E2E tests
```

For memory-constrained environments:
```
OPENCLAW_TEST_PROFILE=low OPENCLAW_TEST_SERIAL_GATEWAY=1 pnpm test
```

Do not set test workers above 16.

## Live Tests (requires real API keys)

```
CLAWDBOT_LIVE_TEST=1 pnpm test:live       # OpenClaw-only live tests
LIVE=1 pnpm test:live                      # Including provider live tests
pnpm test:docker:live-models               # Docker live model tests
pnpm test:docker:live-gateway              # Docker live gateway tests
```

## Test Style

- Prefer per-instance stubs over prototype mutation.
- Only document why prototype-level patching is required if truly needed.
- Pure test additions/fixes generally do NOT need a changelog entry.
